notes: ME Waugh and RT Ponting 219 off 40.2 overs, Australia ODI record 2nd wicket partnership. (previous: GR Marsh and DM Jones 185 v England at Brisbane, 1990/91); 2nd highest partnership for any wicket for Australia (highest: DM Jones and AR Border 224* v Sri Lanka at Adelaide, 1984/85).
RT Ponting 145 off 158 balls, ties the Australia individual record score in ODIs (also: DM Jones 145 v England at Brisbane, 1990/91)
Australia innings: 1x7 ball over (48th over by Streak)

milestones.description: Mark Waugh and Ricky Ponting's 219-run partnership is AUS's highest for the 2nd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 185 between Dean Jones and Geoff Marsh
Ricky Ponting has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (78) in an innings in ODIs for AUS, going past Dean Jones's 72
This is the highest match aggregate (572) involving teams Australia & Zimbabwe in ODIs
